<subSubSection lastPageId="102" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="101.[151,1437,1398,2037]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1759,1785]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Remarks</emphasis>
. All records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[486,641,1759,1784]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[486,641,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">P. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the eastern Pacific, including 
<collectingCountry box="[1043,1132,1759,1785]" name="Panama" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[1147,1290,1758,1785]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref72784" refString="Haig, J. (1957 b) The porcellanid crabs of the &quot; Askoy &quot; expedition to the Panama Bight. American Museum Novitates, 1865, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1957">Haig, 1957b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[1302,1362,1759,1786]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">1960</bibRefCitation>
), were later re-assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chace" authorityYear="1962" box="[380,487,1795,1821]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haigae">
<emphasis box="[380,487,1795,1821]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">P. haigae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chace, F. A. Jr." box="[535,692,1795,1822]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="631 - 633" refId="ref70555" refString="Chace, F. A. Jr. (1962) The non-brachyuran decapod crustaceans of Clipperton Island. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 113 (3466), 631 - 633. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.113 - 3466.605" type="journal article" year="1962">Chace (1962)</bibRefCitation>
. Based on records throughout the Atlantic Ocean, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[1279,1437,1795,1820]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[1279,1437,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">P. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be confined to the more offshore and oceanic conditions, for instance, being the only species found on exposed shores of 
<collectingCountry box="[360,553,1867,1893]" name="Ascension Island" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Ascension Island</collectingCountry>
in the Atlantic Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Manning, R. B. &amp; Chace, F. A. Jr." box="[817,1095,1867,1893]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="1 - 91" refId="ref74439" refString="Manning, R. B. &amp; Chace, F. A. Jr. (1990) Decapod and stomatopod Crustacea from Ascension Island, South Atlantic Ocean. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 503, 1 - 91. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.503" type="journal article" year="1990">Manning &amp; Chace 1990</bibRefCitation>
; De Grave 
<emphasis box="[1225,1283,1867,1893]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">et al.</emphasis>
2017). In the Caribbean Sea and 
<collectingCountry box="[372,443,1903,1929]" name="Brazil" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[455,611,1903,1928]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[455,611,1903,1928]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">P. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported mainly from offshore islands and archipelagos, or exposed shores of larger islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, L. A. A. &amp; Tavares, M." box="[430,714,1939,1965]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="546 - 560" refId="ref71555" refString="Ferreira, L. A. A. &amp; Tavares, M. (2017) A new species of Pachycheles (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae), with taxonomic remarks on two other porcelain crabs from the remote oceanic arquipelago of Trindade and Martin Vaz, South Atlantic Ocean. Zootaxa, 4299 (4), 546 - 560. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4299.4.5" type="journal article" year="2017">Ferreira &amp; Tavares 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poupin, J." box="[727,876,1939,1965]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" refId="ref75876" refString="Poupin, J. (2018) Les crustaces decapodes des Petites Antilles: avec de nouvelles observations pour Saint-Martin, la Guadeloupe et la Martinique. Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 264 pp." type="book" year="2018">Poupin 2018</bibRefCitation>
). The single Panamanian record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[1281,1437,1939,1964]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[1281,1437,1939,1964]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">P. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a specimen from the Gulf of San Bl√°s (Guna Yala) examined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gore, R. H." box="[1026,1165,1975,2001]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref72204" refString="Gore, R. H. (1982) Porcellanid crabs from the coasts of Mexico and Central America (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 363, 1 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.363" type="journal article" year="1982">Gore (1982)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, L. A. A. &amp; Tavares, M." pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="546 - 560" refId="ref71555" refString="Ferreira, L. A. A. &amp; Tavares, M. (2017) A new species of Pachycheles (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae), with taxonomic remarks on two other porcelain crabs from the remote oceanic arquipelago of Trindade and Martin Vaz, South Atlantic Ocean. Zootaxa, 4299 (4), 546 - 560. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4299.4.5" type="journal article" year="2017">Ferreira &amp; Tavares (2017)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
The colour pattern of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[456,613,151,176]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[456,613,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">P. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Central Atlantic (
<collectingCountry box="[930,1049,151,177]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Ascension</collectingCountry>
I.) was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Manning, R. B. &amp; Chace, F. A. Jr." pageId="102" pageNumber="103" pagination="1 - 91" refId="ref74439" refString="Manning, R. B. &amp; Chace, F. A. Jr. (1990) Decapod and stomatopod Crustacea from Ascension Island, South Atlantic Ocean. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 503, 1 - 91. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.503" type="journal article" year="1990">Manning &amp; Chace (1990)</bibRefCitation>
as ‚Äúmottled brick red, with eystalks, articulating membranes and dactyls of walking legs scarlet; ventral surface uniformly scarlet‚Äù. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, L. A. A. &amp; Tavares, M." box="[539,829,223,249]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" pagination="546 - 560" refId="ref71555" refString="Ferreira, L. A. A. &amp; Tavares, M. (2017) A new species of Pachycheles (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae), with taxonomic remarks on two other porcelain crabs from the remote oceanic arquipelago of Trindade and Martin Vaz, South Atlantic Ocean. Zootaxa, 4299 (4), 546 - 560. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4299.4.5" type="journal article" year="2017">Ferreira &amp; Tavares (2017)</bibRefCitation>
published two colour photographs of a specimen from Trindade, a remote island off eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[581,653,259,285]" name="Brazil" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. In this specimen, the carapace has a light lilac-pinkish background, covered with numerous magenta dots; the P2‚ÄìP4 carpi and propodi are dark magenta; the ventral surface is uniformly magenta, except for one large, white, rounded spot on the Mxp3 coxa. The colour pattern of the Caribbean appears to be similar to that of the Brazilian specimens (see black-and-white photograph in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lira, C. &amp; Hernandez, G. &amp; Bolanos, J. &amp; Hernandez, J. &amp; Lopez, R. &amp; Pinate, M. &amp; Hernandez-Avila, I." box="[1085,1263,367,393]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" pagination="19 - 33" refId="ref74251" refString="Lira, C., Hernandez, G., Bolanos, J., Hernandez, J., Lopez, R., Pinate, M. &amp; Hernandez-Avila, I. (2012) Crustaceos decapodos bentonicos litorales de la Isla de La Tortuga. I - Familia Porcellanidae Haworth, 1825. Boletin del Instituto Oceanografico de Venezuela, 51 (1), 19 - 33." type="journal article" year="2012">
Lira 
<emphasis box="[1139,1195,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
